race.description: Flogger&Lois Walsh Memorial & Pom Mates Day Hcp
race.comment: EMPHATIC BEL (8) raced in the leading pair and wouldn't lie down last start over 1000m at Dubbo, clocking in just half a length from the winner in a bold display. Has won at 800m before and back in this easier race he will prove very tough to catch. The widely travelled RUBICON RIVER (9) was in the money last time out at Lockhart picnics over 930m. Has a win over today's journey on the record. Sure to give a good account. DAO SUN (3) disappointed at Grenfell picnics at his latest outing. Wendy Peel gets the best out of this veteran and she has been called upon. Capable of testing this line-up. BRUMMAGEN (6) felt the pinch in the closing stages when resuming at Dubbo recently. Has won here at the trip so with a run under the belt he makes plenty of appeal. MR BINGO (4) wasn't beaten far after leading at Orange last start. Doesn't win often but is worth each-way consideration.
